p.font: 1. Administrator runs Terraform CLI to provision and manage Mastodon infrastructure resources on DigitalOcean.
2. Each resource (DOKS, PostgreSQL, etc.) is provisioned via the DigitalOcean Terraform provider
(uses DigitalOcean REST API under the hood).
3. Terraform creates Kubernetes secrets to store each managed database credentials. Later on, the Kubernetes secrets are referenced by the Helm release to connect to each database.
4. Terraform state file is stored and synced using a dedicated DO Spaces bucket.
